In order to give his people proper representation at the Ibadan North East/ Ibadan South-East federal constituency, a United Kingdom-based Nigerian medical doctor, Kazeem Adesina Olasupo has joined the contest for the House of Representatives ahead of the 2023 general elections. While speaking at the official declaration of his ambition at the Mapo Hall in Ibadan, the Oyo state capital on Thursday, Olasupo said he intended to vie for the position in order to give his people the proper representation they deserved. He stressed that this is the time for people that have good intentions for the country to come out and vie for elective positions. The medical practitioner who hails from the Abidikugu compound in Isale Ijebu area of Ibadan South East local government area said that he will be contesting on the platform of the ruling Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in the state. The PDP chieftain while addressing the people of the two local government areas that make up the federal constituency, promised not to disappoint the constituents. According to him,  “I am here to seek the support of my people in order to represent them in the House of Representatives. I want to represent my people in order to give them the proper representation they deserved. “2023 is very important in the history of this nation. This is the time to build this country. We must put the interest of the country at heart. This is a nation that is full of potential. “This is the time for people who have good intentions for the country to come out to rescue the country. POLL “We don’t have true representation and that is what we are lacking. We need the people that will be accessible by the people. That is why I am contesting to represent my people”.